obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (26853)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title.`
  content `This Act may be called the Punjab Reorganisation Act, 1966.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26853&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (26854)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26854&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,—`
  line
  line `(a) “Administrator” the administrator of a Union territory appointed by the President under`
  line `article 239 of the Constitution;`
  line
  line `(b) “appointed day” means the 1st day of November, 1966;`
  line
  line `(c) “article” means an article of the Constitution;`
  line
  line `(d) “assembly constituency”, “council constituency” and “parliamentary constituency” have the same meanings as in the Representation of the People Act, 1950 (43 of 1950);`
  line
  line `(e) “Delimitation Commission” means the Delimitation Commission constituted under section 3`
  line `of the Delimitation Commission Act, 1962 (61 of 1962);`
  line
  line `(f) “existing State of Punjab” means the State of Punjab as existing immediately before the`
  line `appointed day;`
  line
  line `(g) “law” includes any enactment, ordinance, regulation, order, bye-law, rule, scheme,`
  line `notification or other instrument having, immediately before the appointed day, the force of law in the`
  line `whole or in any part of the existing State of Punjab;`
  line
  line `(h) “notified order” means an order published in the Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `(i) “population ratio”, in relation to the States of Haryana and Punjab and the Union, means the`
  line `ratio of 37.38 to 54.84 to 7.78;`
  line
  line `(j) “prescribed” means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(k) “sitting member”, in relation to either House of Parliament or of the Legislature of the existing`
  line `State of Punjab, means a person who immediately before the appointed day is a member of that`
  line House;
  line
  line `(l) “State of Punjab” means the State with the same name, comprising the territories referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 6;`
  line
  line `(m) “successor State”, in relation to the existing State of Punjab, means the State of Punjab or`
  line `Haryana, and includes also the Union in relation to the Union territory of Chandigarh and the`
  line `transferred territory;`
  line
  line `(n)“transferred territory” means the territory which on the appointed day is transferred from the`
  line `existing State of Punjab to the Union territory of Himachal Pradesh;`
  line
  line `(o) “treasury” includes a sub-treasury; and`
  line
  line `(p) any reference to a district, tahsil or other territorial division of the existing State of Punjab`
  line `shall be construed as a reference to the area comprised within that territorial division on the 1st day of`
  line `July, 1966.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (26855)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Formation of Haryana State.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26855&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) On and from the appointed day, there shall be formed a new`
  line `State to be known as the State of Haryana comprising the following territories of the existing State of`
  line `Punjab, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) Hissar, Rohtak, Gurgaon, Karnal and Mahendragarh districts;`
  line
  line `(b) Norwana and Jind tahsils of Sangrur district;`
  line
  line `(c) Ambala, Jagadhri and Naraingarh tahsils of Ambala district;`
  line
  line `(d) Pinjore kanungo circle of Kharar tahsil of Ambala district; and`
  line
  line `(e) the territories in Manimajra kanungo circle of Kharar tahsil of Ambala district specified in the`
  line `First Schedule,`
  line
  line `and thereupon the said territories shall cease to form part of the existing State of Punjab.`
  line
  line `(2) The territories referred to in clause (b) of sub-section (1) shall form a separate district known as`
  line `the Jind district in the State of Haryana.`
  line
  line `(3) The territories referred to in clauses (c), (d) and (e) of sub-section (1) shall form a separate district`
  line `to be known as Ambala district in the State of Haryana and in that district, —`
  line
  line `(i) the territories referred to in clauses (d) and (e) of sub-section (1) shall be included in, and form`
  line `part of, the Naraingarh tahsil, and`
  line
  line `(ii) the territories referred to in clause (e) of sub-section (1) shall be included in, and form part of,`
  line `Pinjore kanungo circle in the Naraingarh tahsil.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (26856)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Formation of Union territory of Chandigarh.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26856&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `On and from the appointed day, there shall be`
  line `formed a new Union territory to be known as the Union territory of Chandigarh comprising such of the`
  line `territories of Manimajra and Manauli kanungo circles of Kharar tahsil of Ambala district in the existing`
  line `State of Punjab as are specified in the Second Schedule and thereupon the territories so specified shall`
  line `cease to form part of the existing State of Punjab.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (26857)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Transfer of territory from Punjab to Himachal Pradesh.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26857&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) On and from the appointed day,`
  line `there shall be added to the Union territory of Himachal Pradesh the territories in the existing State of`
  line `Punjab comprised in—`
  line
  line `(a) Simla, Kangra, Kulu and Lahaul and Spiti districts;`
  line
  line `(b) Nalagarh tahsil of Ambala district;`
  line
  line `(c) Lohara, Amb and Una kanungo circles of Una tahsil of Hoshiarpur district;`
  line
  line `(d) the territories in Santokhgarh kanungo circle of Una tahsil of Hoshiarpur district specified in`
  line `Part I of the Third Schedule;`
  line
  line `(e) the territories in Una tahsil of Hoshiarpur district specified in Part II of the Third Schedule;`
  line and
  line
  line `(f) the territories of Dhar Kalan kanungo circle of Pathankot tahsil of Gurdaspur district specified`
  line `in Part III of the Third Schedule,`
  line
  line `and thereupon the said territories shall cease to form part of the existing State of Punjab.`
  line
  line `(2) The territories referred to in clause (b) of sub-section (1) shall be included in, and form part of,`
  line `Simla district.`
  line
  line `(3) The territories referred to in clauses (c), (d) and (e) of sub-section (1) shall be included in, and`
  line `form part of, Kangra district, and`
  line
  line `(i) the territories referred to in clauses (c) and (d) shall form a separate tahsil known as Una tahsil`
  line `in that district and in that tahsil the territories referred to in clause (d) shall form a separate kanungo`
  line `circle known as the Santokhgarh kanungo circle; and`
  line
  line `(ii) the territories referred to in clause (e) shall form part of the Hamirpur tahsil in the said`
  line district.
  line
  line `(4) The territories referred to in clause (f) of sub-section (1) shall be included in, and form part of, the`
  line `Bhattiyat tahsil of Chamba district in the Union territory of Himachal Pradesh and in that tahsil, the`
  line `villages Dalhousie and Balun shall be included in, and form part of, Banikhet kanungo circle and the`
  line `village Bakloh shall form part of Chowari kanungo circle.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (26858)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `State of Punjab and territorial divisions thereof.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26858&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) On and from the appointed day, the State`
  line `of Punjab shall comprise the territories of the existing State of Punjab other than those specified in`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 3, section 4 and sub-section (1) of section 5.`
  line
  line `(2) The territories which immediately before the appointed day were part of Ambala district in the`
  line `existing State of Punjab but are not transferred by virtue of sections 3, 4 and 5, shall, together with the`
  line `territories which immediately before that day were part of the Una tahsil of Hoshiarpur district in the`
  line `existing State of Punjab but are not transferred by virtue of section 5, form a separate district known as`
  line `the Rupar district in the State of Punjab and in that district—`
  line
  line `(i) the territories which immediately before the appointed day were part of Manimajra kanungo`
  line `circle of Kharar tahsil of Ambala district but are not transferred by virtue of sections 3 and 4, shall`
  line `form in that tahsil a separate kanungo circle called the Mullanpur kanungo circle;`
  line
  line `(ii) the territories which immediately before the appointed day were part of Una tahsil of`
  line `Hoshiarpur district but are not transferred by virtue of section 5, shall form a separate tahsil known as`
  line `Anandpur Sahib tahsil, and in that tahsil, the territories which immediately before the appointed day`
  line `were part of Santokhgarh kanungo circle of Una tahsil of Hoshiarpur district but are not transferred`
  line `by virtue of section 5, shall be included in, and form part of Nurpur Bedi kanungo circle.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (26859)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Amendment of the First Schedule to the Constitution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26859&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `On and from the appointed day, in the`
  line `First Schedule to the Constitution,—`
  line
  line `(a) under the heading “I. THE STATES”,—`
  line
  line `(i) in the paragraph relating to the territories of the State of Punjab, the following shall be`
  line `added at the end, namely:—`
  line
  line `“and the territories specified in sub-section (1) of section 3, section 4 and sub-section (1) of section 5 of the Punjab Reorganisation Act, 1966”;`
  line
  line `(ii) after entry 16, the following entry shall be inserted, namely:—`
  line
  line `“17. Haryana… The territories specified in sub-section (1) of section 3 of the Punjab`
  line
  line `Reorganisation Act, 1966”;`
  line
  line `(b) under the heading “II. THE UNION TERRITORIES”,—`
  line
  line `(i) in the paragraph relating to the extent of the Union territory of Himachal Pradesh, the`
  line `following shall be added at the end, namely:—`
  line
  line `“and the territories specified in sub-section (1) of section 5 of the Punjab Reorganisation Act, 1966”;`
  line
  line `(ii) after entry 9, the following entry shall be inserted, namely:—`
  line
  line `“10. Chandigarh… The territories specified in section 4 of the Punjab Reorganisation`
  line
  line `Act, 1966.”.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (26860)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Saving powers of Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26860&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in the foregoing provisions of this Part shall be deemed`
  line `to affect the power of the Government of Punjab or Haryana or the Administrator of the Union territory of Himachal Pradesh to alter, after the appointed day, the name, area or boundaries of any district or other`
  line `territorial division in the State or Union territory, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (26861)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Amendment of the Fourth Schedule to the Constitution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26861&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `On and from the appointed day, in the`
  line `Fourth Schedule to the Constitution, in the Table,—`
  line
  line `(a) entries 5 to 21 shall be re-numbered as entries 6 to 22 respectively;`
  line
  line `(b) after entry 4, the following entry shall be inserted, namely:—`
  line
  line `“5. Haryana....5”;`
  line
  line `(c) in entry 12 as so re-numbered, for the figures “11”, the figure “7” shall be substituted;`
  line
  line `(d) in entry 19 as so re-numbered, for the figure “2”, the figure “3” shall be substituted; and`
  line
  line `(e) for the figures “226”, the figures “228” shall be substituted.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (26862)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Allocation of sitting members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26862&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) On and from the appointed day, the eleven sitting members`
  line `of the Council of States representing the existing State of Punjab shall be deemed to have been elected to`
  line `fill the seats allotted to the States of Haryana and Punjab and the Union territory of Himachal Pradesh, as`
  line `specified in the Fourth Schedule.`
  line
  line `(2) The term of office of such sitting members shall remain unaltered.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (26863)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Filling up of vacancies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26863&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) As soon as may be after the appointed day, bye-elections shall be`
  line `held to fill the vacancies existing on the appointed day in the seats allotted to the State of Haryana.`
  line
  line `(2) The term of office of such one of the two members so elected, as the Chairman of the Council of`
  line `States may determine by drawing lot, shall expire on the 2nd day of April, 1968, and the term of office of`
  line `the other member shall expire on the 2nd day of April, 1972.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (26864)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Provision as to existing House.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26864&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in Part II shall be deemed to affect the constitution or`
  line `duration of the existing House of the People or the extent of the constituency of any sitting member of`
  line `that House.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (26865)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Provisions as to Legislative Assemblies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26865&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) The number of seats as on the appointed day in the`
  line `Legislative Assemblies of the States of Haryana and Punjab and the Union territory of Himachal Pradesh`
  line `shall be fifty-four, eighty-seven and fifty-six respectively.`
  line
  line `(2) In the Second Schedule to the Representation of the People Act, 1950 (43 of 1950)—`
  line
  line `(a) after entry 4, the following entry shall be inserted, namely:—`
  line
  line `“4A. Haryana . . . 54”;`
  line
  line `(b) in entry 11, for the figures “154”, the figures “87” shall be substituted; and`
  line
  line `(c) in entry 16, for the figures “40”, the figures “54” shall be substituted.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (26866)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Amendment of Delimitation Orders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26866&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `On and from the appointed day, Part B of Schedule XI to`
  line `the Delimitation of Parliamentary and Assembly Constituencies Order, 1961, and the Schedule to the`
  line `Delimitation of Territorial Council Constituencies (Himachal Pradesh) Order, 1962, shall stand amended`
  line `as directed in the Fifth Schedule to this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (26867)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Allocation of sitting members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26867&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every sitting member of the Legislative Assembly of`
  line `Punjab elected to fill a seat in that Assembly from a constituency which on the appointed day by virtue of`
  line `the provisions of section 14 stands allotted, with or without alteration of boundaries, to the State of Haryana or to the Union territory of Himachal Pradesh, shall, on and from that day, cease to be a member`
  line `of the Legislative Assembly of Punjab and shall be deemed to have been elected to fill a seat in the`
  line `Legislative Assembly of Haryana or in the Legislative Assembly of Himachal Pradesh, as the case may`
  line `be, from that constituency as so allotted.`
  line
  line `(2) All other sitting members of the Legislative Assembly of Punjab shall continue to be members of`
  line `the Legislative Assembly of that State and any such sitting member representing a constituency the`
  line `extent, or the name and extent, of which are altered by virtue of the provisions of section 14 shall be`
  line `deemed to have been elected to the Legislative Assembly of Punjab by that constituency as so altered.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force, the Legislative`
  line `Assemblies of Haryana, Punjab and Himachal Pradesh shall be deemed to be duly constituted on the`
  line `appointed day.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (26868)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Duration of Legislative Assembly of Haryana.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26868&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `The period of five years referred to in`
  line `clause (1) of article 172 shall, in the case of the Legislative Assembly of Haryana, be deemed to have`
  line `commenced on the date on which it actually commenced in the case of the Legislative Assembly of`
  line Punjab.
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (26869)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Duration of Legislative Assemblies of Punjab and Himachal Pradesh.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26869&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `The changes in the`
  line `composition of the Legislative Assemblies of Punjab and Himachal Pradesh shall not affect the duration`
  line `of either of those Assemblies.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (26870)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Speakers and Deputy Speakers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26870&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) The person who immediately before the appointed day is`
  line `the Speaker of the Legislative Assembly of Punjab shall continue to be the Speaker of that Assembly on`
  line `and from that day.`
  line
  line `(2) As soon as may be after the appointed day, the Legislative Assembly of Haryana shall choose a`
  line `member of that Assembly to be Speaker of that Assembly.`
  line
  line `(3) The person who immediately before the appointed day is the Deputy Speaker of the Legislative`
  line `Assembly of Punjab shall be the Deputy Speaker of the Legislative Assembly of Haryana.`
  line
  line `(4) As soon as may be after the appointed day, the Legislative Assembly of Punjab shall choose a`
  line `member of that Assembly to be Deputy Speaker of that Assembly.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (26871)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Rules of procedure.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26871&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `The rules of procedure and conduct of business of the Legislative`
  line `Assembly of Punjab as in force immediately before the appointed day shall, until rules are made under`
  line `clause (1) of article 208, be the rules of procedure and conduct of business of the Legislative Assembly of`
  line `Haryana, subject to such modifications and adaptations as may be made therein by the Speaker thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (26872)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Legislative Council of Punjab.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26872&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `On and from the appointed day, there shall be forty seats in the`
  line `Legislative Council of Punjab, and in the Third Schedule to the Representation of the People Act, 1950`
  line `(43 of 1950), for the existing entry 7, the following entry shall be substituted, namely:—`
  line
  line `"7. Punjab . . 40 14 3 3 14 6".`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (26873)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Council constituencies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26873&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `On and from the appointed day, the Delimitation of Council`
  line `Constituencies (Punjab) Order, 1951, shall stand amended as directed in the Sixth Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (26874)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Provision as to certain sitting members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26874&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) On the appointed day, the sitting members of the`
  line `Legislative Council of Punjab specified in the Seventh Schedule shall cease to be members of that`
  line Council.
  line
  line `(2) On and from the appointed day, all sitting members of the Legislative Council of Punjab, other`
  line `than those referred to in sub-section (1), shall continue to be members of that Council.`
  line
  line `(3) Any of the sitting members continuing as aforesaid, representing a council constituency the extent`
  line `of which is altered by virtue of the provisions of section 21 shall be deemed to have been elected to the`
  line `Legislative Council of Punjab by that constituency as so altered.`
  line
  line `(4) Every sitting member of the said Council representing immediately before the appointed day any`
  line `of the council constituencies specified in column (1) of the Table below shall be deemed to have been`
  line `elected to the said Council by the council constituency specified against that constituency in column (2)`
  line `of the said Table:—`
  line
  line TABLE
  line
  line `(1) (2)`
  line
  line `Punjab West Central Graduates Punjab Central Graduates.`
  line
  line `Punjab East Central Graduates Punjab South Graduates.`
  line
  line `Punjab West Central Teachers Punjab Central Teachers.`
  line
  line `Punjab East Central Teachers Punjab South Teachers.`
  line
  line `Patiala Local Authorities Patiala-cum-Rupar Local Authorities.`
  line
  line `(5) The term of office of the members referred to in sub-section (2) shall remain unaltered.`
  line
  line `(6) As soon as may be after the appointed day, elections shall be held to fill the vacancies existing on`
  line `the appointed day in the seats allotted to the several council constituencies by the Delimitation of Council`
  line `Constituencies (Punjab) Order, 1951, as amended by this Act and to fill the vacancy existing on that day`
  line `in the seats to be filled by persons elected by the members of the Legislative Assembly.`
  line
  line `(7) The term of office of the three members so elected from Ferozepur Local Authorities`
  line `constituency, Jullundur Local Authorities constitutency and Ludhiana Local Authorities constituency`
  line `and of the member so elected by the members of the Legislative Assembly shall expire on the 26th day of`
  line `April, 1968, and the term of office of the member so elected from Patiala-cum-Rupar Local Authorities`
  line `constituency shall expire on the 26th day of April, 1972.`
  line
  line `(8) The person who immediately before the appointed day is the Chairman of the Legislative Council`
  line `of Punjab shall continue to be the Chairman of that Council on and from that day.`
  line
  line `(9) As soon as may be after the appointed day, the Legislative Council of Punjab shall choose one of`
  line `its members to be the Deputy Chairman thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (26875)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Allocation of seats in the House of the People.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26875&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `In the House of the People to be constituted`
  line `after the commencement of this Act, there shall be allotted,—`
  line
  line `(a) nine seats to the State of Haryana of which two seats shall be reserved for the Scheduled`
  line Castes;
  line
  line `(b) thirteen seats to the State of Punjab of which three seats shall be reserved for the Scheduled`
  line Castes;
  line
  line `(c) six seats to the Union territory of Himachal Pradesh of which one seat shall be reserved for the`
  line `Scheduled Castes; and`
  line
  line `(d) one seat to the Union territory of Chandigarh which shall form one Parliamentary`
  line constituency.
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (26876)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Allocation of seats in the Legislative Assembly.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26876&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) The total number of seats in the`
  line `Legislative Assembly of Haryana to be constituted at any time after the appointed day, to be filled by`
  line `persons chosen by direct election from territorial constituencies, shall be eighty-one of which fifteen seats`
  line `shall be reserved for the Scheduled Castes.`
  line
  line `(2) The total number of seats in the Legislative Assembly of Punjab to be constituted at any time after`
  line `the appointed day, to be filled by persons chosen by direct election from territorial constituencies, shall be`
  line `one hundred and four of which twenty-three seats shall be reserved for the Scheduled Castes.`
  line
  line `(3) The total number of seats in the Legislative Assembly of Himachal Pradesh to be constituted at`
  line `any time after the appointed day, to be filled by persons chosen by direct election from territorial`
  line `constituencies, shall be sixty of which fourteen seats shall be reserved for the Scheduled Castes and three`
  line `seats shall be reserved for the Scheduled Tribes.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (26877)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Delimitation of constituencies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26877&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Delimitation Commission shall, in the manner herein`
  line `provided, distribute the seats in the House of the People allotted to Haryana, Punjab and Himachal`
  line `Pradesh under section 23 and the seats assigned to the Legislative Assembly of each of them under`
  line `section 24 to single-member territorial constituencies and delimit them on the basis of the latest census`
  line `figures, having regard to the provisions of the Constitution and to the following provisions, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) all constituencies shall, as far as practicable be geographically compact areas, and in`
  line `delimiting them regard shall be had to physical features, existing boundaries of administrative units,`
  line `facilities of communication and public convenience;`
  line
  line `(b) every assembly constituency shall be so delimited as to fall wholly within one parliamentary`
  line constituency;
  line
  line `(c) constituencies in which seats are reserved for the Scheduled Castes shall be distributed in`
  line `different parts of the State or Union territory, as the case may be, and located, as far as practicable, in`
  line `those areas where the proportion of their population to the total population is comparatively large; and`
  line
  line `(d) constituencies in which seats are reserved for the Scheduled Tribes shall, as far as practicable,`
  line `be located in areas where the proportion of their population to the total population is the largest.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purpose of assisting it in the performance of its functions under sub-section (1), the`
  line `Delimitation Commission shall associate with itself in respect of each State and Union territory such six`
  line `persons as the Central Government may by order specify, being persons who are members either of the`
  line `House of the People or of the Legislative Assembly of Haryana, Punjab or Himachal Pradesh:`
  line
  line `Provided that such persons shall be chosen, as far as practicable, from among those members who`
  line `were associated before the commencement of this Act with the Delimitation Commission in delimiting`
  line `constituencies of Punjab or Himachal Pradesh:`
  line
  line `Provided further that none of the associate members shall have a right to vote or to sign any decision`
  line `of the Delimitation Commission.`
  line
  line `(3) The Delimitation Commission shall, by one or more orders, determine the delimitation of the`
  line `parliamentary and assembly constituencies referred to in sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(4) The provisions of sections 7, 10 and 11 of the Delimitation Commission Act, 1962 (61 of 1962),`
  line `shall apply in relation to the delimitation of parliamentary and assembly constituencies under this Part as`
  line `they apply in relation to the delimitation of parliamentary and assembly constituencies under the said Act.`
  line
  line `(5) Upon publication in the Gazette of India of the order or orders of the Delimitation Commission`
  line `made under sub-section (3), the orders previously made by it delimiting the parliamentary and assembly`
  line `constituencies of Punjab and Himachal Pradesh shall stand cancelled.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (26878)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Amendment of article 371 of the Constitution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26878&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `.On and from the appointed day, in article 371`
  line `of the Constitution, in clause (1), the words "or Punjab" shall be omitted.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (26879)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Amendment of Scheduled Castes Orders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26879&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) On and from the appointed day, the Constitution`
  line `(Scheduled Castes) Order, 1950, shall stand amended as directed in the Eighth Schedule.`
  line
  line `(2) On and from the appointed day, the Constitution (Scheduled Castes) (Union Territories) Order,`
  line `1951, shall stand amended as directed in the Ninth Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (26880)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Amendment of Scheduled Tribes Orders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26880&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) On and from the appointed day, the Constitution`
  line `(Scheduled Tribes) Order, 1950, shall stand amended as directed in the Tenth Schedule.`
  line
  line `(2) On and from the appointed day, the Constitution (Scheduled Tribes) (Union Territories) Order,`
  line `1951, shall stand amended as directed in the Eleventh Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (26881)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Common High Court for Punjab, Haryana and Chandigarh.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26881&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) On and from the appointed`
  line day,—
  line
  line `(a) there shall be a common High Court for the States of Punjab and Haryana and for the Union`
  line `territory of Chandigarh to be called the High Court of Punjab and Haryana (hereinafter referred to as`
  line `the common High Court);`
  line
  line `(b) the Judges of the High Court of Punjab holding office immediately before that day shall,`
  line `unless they have elected otherwise, become on that day the Judges of the common High Court.`
  line
  line `(2) The expenditure in respect of salaries and allowances of the Judges of the common High Court`
  line `shall be allocated amongst the States of Punjab and Haryana and the Union territory of Chandigarh in`
  line `such proportion as the President may, by order, determine.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (26882)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Jurisdiction of the common High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26882&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `On and from the appointed day, the common High`
  line `Court shall have, in respect of the territories comprised in the States of Punjab and Haryana and the Union`
  line `territory of Chandigarh, all such jurisdiction, powers and authority as, under the law in force immediately`
  line `before the appointed day, are exercisable in respect of those territories by the High Court of Punjab and`
  line `shall, save as otherwise provided in this Part, have no jurisdiction in respect of the transferred territory.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (26883)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Special provision relating to Bar Council and Advocates.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26883&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) On and from the appointed`
  line day,—
  line
  line `(a) in the Advocates Act, 1961 (25 of 1961), in sub-section (1) of section 3, for clause (d), the`
  line `following clause shall be substituted, namely:—`
  line
  line `“(d) for the States of Punjab and Haryana and the Union territories of Chandigarh and Himachal Pradesh, to be known as the Bar Council of Punjab and Haryana”;`
  line
  line `(b) the Bar Council of Punjab shall be deemed to be the Bar Council of Punjab and Haryana with`
  line `the Advocate-General of the State of Haryana also as an ex officio member.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person who immediately before the appointed day is an advocate entitled to practice in the`
  line `High Court of Punjab shall be entitled to practise as an advocate in the common High Court.`
  line
  line `(3) All persons who immediately before the appointed day are advocates on the roll of the Bar`
  line `Council of Punjab shall, as from that day, become advocates on the roll of the Bar Council of Punjab and`
  line Haryana.
  line
  line `(4) The right of audience in the common High Court shall be regulated in accordance with the like`
  line `principles as immediately before the appointed day are in force with respect to the right of audience in the`
  line `High Court of Punjab:`
  line
  line `Provided that as between the Advocate-General of Punjab and the Advocate-General of Haryana, the`
  line `right of audience shall be determined with reference to their dates of enrolment as advocates.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (26884)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Practice and procedure in common High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26884&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of this Part, the law`
  line `in force immediately before the appointed day with respect to practice and procedure in the High Court of`
  line `Punjab shall, with the necessary modifications, apply in relation to the common High Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (26885)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Custody of seal of common High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26885&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `The law in force immediately before the appointed`
  line `day with respect to the custody of the seal of the High Court of Punjab shall, with the necessary`
  line `modifications, apply with respect to the custody of the seal of the common High Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (26886)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Form of writs and other processes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26886&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `The law in force immediately before the appointed day`
  line `with respect to the form of writs and other processes used, issued or awarded by the High Court of Punjab`
  line `shall, with the necessary modifications, apply with respect to the form of writs and other processes used,`
  line `issued or awarded by the common High Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (26887)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Powers of Judges.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26887&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `The law in force immediately before the appointed day with respect to the`
  line `powers of the Chief Justice, single Judges and division courts of the High Court of Punjab and with`
  line `respect to all matters ancillary to the exercise of those powers shall, with the necessary modifications,`
  line `apply in relation to the common High Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (26888)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Principal seat and other places of sitting of the common High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26888&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `(1) The principal seat`
  line `of the common High Court shall, unless otherwise determined by the President after consultation with the`
  line `Chief Justice of that High Court and the Governors of Punjab and Haryana, be at the same place as the`
  line `principal seat of the High Court of Punjab immediately before the appointed day.`
  line
  line `(2) The President may, after consultation with the Chief Justice of the common High Court and the`
  line `Governors of the States of Punjab and Haryana, by notified order, provide for the establishment of a`
  line `permanent bench or benches of that High Court at one or more places within the territories to which the`
  line `jurisdiction of the High Court extends, other than the principal seat of the High Court, and for any`
  line `matters connected therewith.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1) or sub-section (2), the Judges and division`
  line `courts of the common High Court may also sit at such other place or places in the States of Punjab and`
  line `Haryana as the Chief Justice may, with the approval of the Governors of the States of Punjab and`
  line `Haryana, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (26889)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Procedure as to appeals to Supreme Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26889&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `The law in force immediately before the`
  line `appointed day relating to appeals to the Supreme Court from the High Court of Punjab and the Judges and`
  line `division courts thereof, shall, with the necessary modifications, apply in relation to the common High`
  line Court.
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (26890)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Extension of jurisdiction of the Court of Judicial Commissioner for Himachal Pradesh.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26890&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line On
  line `and from the appointed day, the jurisdiction of the Court of the Judicial Commissioner for Himachal`
  line `Pradesh shall extend to the transferred territory.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (26891)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `Transfer of pending proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26891&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `(1) All proceedings pending in the High Court of Punjab`
  line `immediately before the appointed day shall, on that day, stand transferred to the common High Court.`
  line
  line `(2) Such proceedings which stand transferred to the common High Court under sub-section (1) as are`
  line `certified by the Chief Justice of the common High Court, having regard to the place of accrual of the`
  line `cause of action and other circumstances, to be proceedings which ought to be heard and decided by the`
  line `Court of the Judicial Commissioner for Himachal Pradesh shall, as soon as may be after such`
  line `certification, be transferred to the Court of the Judicial Commissioner for Himachal Pradesh.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in the foregoing provisions of this Part, but save as`
  line `hereinafter provided, the common High Court shall have, and the Court of the Judicial Commissioner for`
  line `Himachal Pradesh shall not have, jurisdiction to entertain, hear or dispose of appeals, applications for`
  line `leave to appeal to the Supreme Court, applications for review and other proceedings where any such`
  line `proceedings seek any relief in respect of any order passed by the High Court of Punjab before the`
  line `appointed day:`
  line
  line `Provided that if, after any such proceedings have been entertained by the common High Court, it`
  line `appears to the Chief Justice of that High Court that they ought to be transferred to the Court of the`
  line `Judicial Commissioner for Himachal Pradesh, he shall order that they shall be so transferred, and such`
  line `proceedings shall thereupon be transferred accordingly.`
  line
  line `(4) Any order—`
  line
  line `(a) made by the High Court of Punjab before the appointed day, in any proceeding transferred to`
  line `the Court of the Judicial Commissioner for Himachal Pradesh by virtue of sub-section (2), or`
  line
  line `(b) made by the common High Court in any proceeding with respect to which that High Court has`
  line `jurisdiction by virtue of sub-section (3),`
  line
  line `shall for all purposes have effect not only as an order of the High Court of Punjab or, as the case may be,`
  line `of the common High Court, but also as an order made by the Court of the Judicial Commissioner for`
  line `Himachal Pradesh.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (26892)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title Interpretation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26892&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `For the purposes of this Part,—`
  line
  line `(a) proceedings shall be deemed to be pending in a court until that court has disposed of all issues`
  line `between the parties including any issues with respect to the taxation of the costs of the proceedings`
  line `and shall include appeals, applications for leave to appeal to the Supreme Court, applications for`
  line `review, petitions for revision and petitions for writs; and`
  line
  line `(b) references to a High Court shall be construed as including references to a Judge or division`
  line `court thereof, and references to an order made by a court or a Judge shall be construed as including`
  line `references to a sentence, judgment or decree passed or made by that court or Judge.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (26893)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title Savings.
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26893&sectionno=41&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in this Part shall affect the application to the common High Court of any`
  line `provisions of the Constitution, and this Part shall have effect subject to any provision that may be made`
  line `on or after the appointed day with respect to that High Court by any Legislature or other authority having`
  line `power to make such provision.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (26894)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 42
  title `Authorisation of expenditure of the State of Haryana.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26894&sectionno=42&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `The Governor of the existing State of`
  line `Punjab may at any time, before the appointed day, authorise such expenditure from the Consolidated`
  line `Fund of the State of Haryana as he deems necessary for any period not extending beyond the 31st day of`
  line `March, 1967, pending the sanction of such expenditure by the Legislative Assembly of Haryana:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Governor of Haryana may, after the appointed day, authorise such further`
  line `expenditure from the Consolidated Fund of the State as he deems necessary for the said period pending`
  line `such sanction.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (26895)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 43
  title `Appropriation of moneys for expenditure in transferred territory.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26895&sectionno=43&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `(1) On and from the`
  line `appointed day, any Act passed by the Legislative Assembly of the Union territory of Himachal Pradesh`
  line `before that day for the appropriation of any money out of the Consolidated Fund of that Union Territory`
  line `to meet any expenditure in respect of any part of the financial year 1966-67 shall have effect also in`
  line `relation to the transferred territory and it shall be lawful for the Government of Himachal Pradesh to`
  line `spend any amount in the transferred territory out of the amount authorised by such Act to be expended for`
  line `any service in that Union territory.`
  line
  line `(2) The Administrator of Himachal Pradesh may, after the appointed day, authorise such expenditure`
  line `from the Consolidated Fund of the Union territory as he deems necessary for any purpose or service in the`
  line `transferred territory for any period not extending beyond the 31st day of March, 1967, pending the`
  line `sanction of such expenditure by the Legislative Assembly of Himachal Pradesh.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (26896)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 44
  title `Reports relating to the accounts of the existing State of Punjab.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26896&sectionno=44&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `(1) The reports of the`
  line `Comptroller and Auditor-General of India referred to in clause (2) of article 151 relating to the accounts`
  line `of the existing State of Punjab in respect of any period prior to the appointed day, shall be submitted to`
  line `the Governor of each of the States of Punjab and Haryana and the Administrator of Himachal Pradesh`
  line `who shall cause them to be laid before the Legislature of that State or Union territory, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) The President may by order—`
  line
  line `(a) declare any expenditure incurred out of the Consolidated Fund of Punjab on any service in`
  line `respect of any period prior to the appointed day during the financial year 1966-67 or in respect of any`
  line `earlier financial year in excess of the amount granted for that service and for that year as disclosed in`
  line `the reports referred to in sub-section (1) to have been duly authorised, and`
  line
  line `(b) provide for any action to be taken on any matter arising out of the said reports.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (26897)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 45
  title `Allowances and privileges of Governor of Haryana.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26897&sectionno=45&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `The allowances and privileges of the`
  line `Governor of Haryana shall, until provision in that behalf is made by Parliament by law under clause (3) of`
  line `article 158, be such as the President may, by order, determine.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (26898)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 46
  title `Distribution of revenues.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26898&sectionno=46&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `The Constitution (Distribution of Revenues) Order, 1965, the Union`
  line `Duties of Excise (Distribution) Act, 1962 (3 of 1962), the Additional Duties of Excise (Goods of Special Importance) Act, 1957 (58 of 1957), and the Estate Duty (Distribution) Act 1962, (9 of 1962), shall on`
  line `and from the appointed day, stand amended as directed in the Twelfth Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (26899)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 47
  title `Application of Part.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26899&sectionno=47&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Part shall apply in relation to the apportionment of`
  line `the assets and liabilities of the existing State of Punjab immediately before the appointed day.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (26900)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 48
  title `Land and goods.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26900&sectionno=48&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the other provisions of this Part, all land and all stores, articles`
  line `and other goods belonging to the existing State of Punjab shall,`
  line
  line `(a) if within that State, pass to the successor State in whose territories they are situated; or`
  line
  line `(b) if outside that State, pass to the State of Punjab:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the Central Government is of the opinion that any goods or class of goods should`
  line `be distributed among the successor States otherwise than according to the situation of the goods, the`
  line `Central Government may issue such directions as it thinks fit for a just and equitable distribution of the`
  line `goods and the goods shall pass to the successor States accordingly.`
  line
  line `(2) Stores held for specific purposes, such as use or utilisation in particular institutions, workshops or`
  line `undertakings or on particular works under construction, shall pass to the successor State in whose`
  line `territories such institutions, workshops, undertakings or works are located.`
  line
  line `(3) Stores relating to the Secretariat and offices of Heads of Departments having jurisdiction over the`
  line `whole of the existing State of Punjab shall be divided between the successor States in accordance with`
  line `such directions as the Central Government may think fit to issue for a just and equitable distribution of`
  line `such stores.`
  line
  line `(4) Any other unissued stores of any class in the existing State of Punjab shall be divided between the`
  line `successor States in proportion to the total stores of that class purchased in the period of three years ending`
  line `with the 31st day of March, 1966, for the territories of the existing State of Punjab included respectively`
  line `in each of the successor States:`
  line
  line `Provided that where such proportion cannot be ascertained in respect of any class of stores or where`
  line `the value of any class of such stores does not exceed rupees ten thousand, that class of stores shall be`
  line `divided between the successor States according to the population ratio.`
  line
  line `(5) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, the lands specified in the Thirteenth Schedule`
  line `which were acquired by the Government of the existing State of Punjab`
  line
  line `(i) for the sewerage scheme of Chandigarh,`
  line
  line `(ii) for soil conservation measures in the catchment area of Sukhna lake, and`
  line
  line `(iii) for the setting up of brick kilns of the Chandigarh Capital Project,`
  line
  line `together with all connected works in or over such land (including any plant, machinery or implements)`
  line `shall vest in the Union.`
  line
  line `(6) In this section, the expression "land" includes immovable property of every kind and any rights in`
  line `or over such property, and the expression "goods" does not include coins, bank notes and currency notes.`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (26901)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 49
  title `Treasury and bank balances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26901&sectionno=49&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `The total of the cash balances in all treasuries of the existing`
  line `State of Punjab and the credit balances of that State with the Reserve Bank of India, the State Bank of`
  line `India or any other bank immediately before the appointed day shall be divided between the successor`
  line `States according to the population ratio:`
  line
  line `Provided that for the purposes of such division, there shall be no transfer of cash balances from any`
  line `treasury to any other treasury and the apportionment shall be effected by adjusting the credit balances of`
  line `the successor States in the books of the Reserve Bank of India on the appointed day:`
  line
  line `Provided further that if any successor State has no account with the Reserve Bank of India, the`
  line `adjustment shall be made in such manner as the Central Government may by order, direct.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (26902)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 50
  title `Arrears of taxes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26902&sectionno=50&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `The right to recover arrears of any tax or duty on property, including arrears`
  line `of land revenue, shall belong to the successor State in whose territories the property is situated, and the`
  line `right to recover arrears of any other tax or duty shall belong to the successor State in whose territories the`
  line `place of assessment of that tax or duty is included.`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (26903)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 51
  title `Right to recover loans and advances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26903&sectionno=51&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `(1) The right to recover any loans or advances made`
  line `before the appointed day by the existing State of Punjab to any local body, society, agriculturist or other`
  line `person in an area within that State shall belong to the successor State in whose territories that area is`
  line `included:`
  line
  line `Provided that the right to recover loans or advances of pay and travelling allowance to a Government`
  line `servant made before the appointed day by the existing State of Punjab shall pass to the successor State to`
  line `which such Government servant is allotted.`
  line
  line `(2) The right to recover any loans or advances made before the appointed day by the existing State of`
  line `Punjab to any person or institution outside that State shall belong to the State of Punjab:`
  line
  line `Provided that any sum recovered in respect of any such loan or advance shall be divided between all`
  line `the successor States according to the population ratio.`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (26904)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 52
  title `Investments and credits in certain funds.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26904&sectionno=52&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `(1) The investments made from the Cash Balance`
  line `Investment Account, the Famine Relief Fund and any other general fund of the existing State of Punjab,`
  line `the sums at the credit of that State in the Central Road Fund and the sums held in the Defence and`
  line `Security Relief Fund shall be divided between the successor States according to the population ratio; and`
  line `the investments in any special fund the objects of which are confined to a local area in the existing State`
  line `of Punjab shall pass to the successor State in whose territories that area is included.`
  line
  line `(2) The investments of the existing State of Punjab immediately before the appointed day in any`
  line `private commercial or industrial undertaking, in so far as such investments have not been made or are`
  line `deemed not to have been made from the Cash Balance Investment Account, shall pass to the successor`
  line `State in whose territories the principal seat of business of the undertaking is located and where on that day`
  line `the principal seat of business of the undertaking is located outside the territories of the existing State of`
  line `Punjab such investments shall be divided between all the successor States in the population ratio.`
  line
  line `(3) Where anybody corporate constituted under a Central Act, State Act or Provincial Act for the`
  line `existing State of Punjab or any part thereof has, by virtue of the provisions of Part II, become an interState`
  line `body corporate, the investments in, or loans or advances to, any such body corporate by the existing`
  line `State of Punjab made before the appointed day shall, save as otherwise expressly provided by or under`
  line `this Act, be divided between the successor States in the same proportion in which the assets of the body`
  line `corporate are divided under the provisions of Part VII.`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (26905)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 53
  title `Assets and liabilities of State undertakings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26905&sectionno=53&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `(1) The assets and liabilities relating to any`
  line `commercial or industrial undertaking of the existing State of Punjab shall pass to the successor State in`
  line `whose territories the undertaking is located.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a depreciation reserve fund is maintained by the existing State of Punjab for any`
  line `commercial or industrial undertaking, the securities held in respect of investments made from that fund`
  line `shall pass to the successor State in whose territories the undertaking is located.`
  line
  line `(3) Where any such undertaking is located in more than one successor State, the assets and liabilities`
  line `and the securities referred to in sub-sections (1) and (2) respectively shall be divided in such manner as`
  line `may be agreed upon between the successor States before the 1st day of November, 1967, or in default of`
  line `such agreement, as the Central Government may by order direct.`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (26906)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 54
  title `Public debt.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26906&sectionno=54&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `(1) The public debt of the existing State of Punjab attributable to loans raised by`
  line `the issue of Government securities and outstanding with the public immediately before the appointed day`
  line `shall, on and from that day, be the debt of the State of Punjab, and—`
  line
  line `(a) the other successor States shall be liable to pay to the State of Punjab their shares of the sums`
  line `due from time to time for the servicing and repayment of the debt, and`
  line
  line `(b) for the purpose of determining the said shares, the debt shall be deemed to be divided between`
  line `the successor States as if it were a debt referred to in sub-section (4).`
  line
  line `(2) The public debt of the existing State of Punjab attributable to loans taken from the Central`
  line `Government, the National Co-operative Development Corporation or the Khadi and Village Industries`
  line `Commission or from any other source for the purpose of re-lending the same to a specific institution or`
  line `class of institutions and outstanding immediately before the appointed day shall—`
  line
  line `(a) if re-lent to any local body, body corporate or other institution in any local area, be the debt of`
  line `the successor State in whose territories the local area is included on the appointed day; or`
  line
  line `(b) if re-lent to the Punjab State Electricity Board or any other institution which becomes an interState`
  line `institution on the appointed day, be divided between the successor States in the same proportion`
  line `in which the assets of such body corporate or institution are divided under the provisions of Part VII.`
  line
  line `(3) The public debt of the existing State of Punjab attributable to loans taken from the Central`
  line `Government for the Beas Project and the Bhakra-Nangal Project as defined in sub-section (4) of`
  line `section 78 shall be divided between the successor States in such proportion as may be agreed upon`
  line `between them, or if no agreement is entered into within two years from the appointed day, as may be`
  line `fixed by order of the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(4) The remaining public debt of the existing State of Punjab attributable to loans taken from the`
  line `Central Government, the Reserve Bank of India or any other body or bank before the appointed day shall`
  line `be divided between the successor States in proportion to the total expenditure on all capital works and`
  line `other capital outlays incurred or deemed to have been incurred up to the appointed day in the territories of`
  line `the existing State of Punjab included respectively in each of those successor States:`
  line
  line `Provided that in computing such expenditure, the expenditure on the Beas Project and the`
  line `Bhakra-Nangal Project as defined in sub- section (4) of section 78 shall be excluded and the expenditure`
  line `on other assets for which capital accounts have been kept shall be taken into account.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—Where any expenditure on capital works or other capital outlays cannot be allocated`
  line `between the territories included in the successor States, such expenditure shall, for the purposes of this`
  line `sub-section, be deemed to have been incurred in those territories according to the population ratio.`
  line
  line `(5) Where a sinking fund or depreciation fund is maintained by the existing State of Punjab for`
  line `repayment of any loan referred to in sub-section (3), the securities held in respect of the investments made`
  line `from that fund shall be divided between the successor States in the same proportion and in the same`
  line `manner as the public debt referred to in sub-section (3).`
  line
  line `(6) Where a sinking fund or depreciation fund is maintained by the existing State of Punjab for the`
  line `repayment of any loan raised by it other than a loan referred to in sub-section (3), the securities held in`
  line `respect of the investments made from that fund shall be divided between the successor States in the same`
  line `proportion as the public debt referred to in sub-section (4).`
  line
  line `(7) In this section, the expression "Government security" means a security created and issued by a`
  line `State Government for the purpose of raising a public loan and having any of the forms specified in, or`
  line `prescribed under clause (2) of section 2 of the Public Debt Act, 1944 (18 of 1944).`
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (26907)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 55
  title `Refund of taxes collected in excess.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26907&sectionno=55&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `The liability of the existing State of Punjab to refund any`
  line `tax or duty on property, including land revenue, collected in excess shall be the liability of the successor`
  line `State in whose territories the property is situated, and the liability of the existing State of Punjab to refund`
  line `any other tax or duty collected in excess shall be the liability of the successor State in whose territories`
  line `the place of assessment of that tax or duty is included.`
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (26908)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 56
  title `Deposits, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26908&sectionno=56&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `(1) The liability of the existing State of Punjab in respect of any civil deposit or`
  line `local fund deposit shall, on and from the appointed day, be the liability of the successor State in whose`
  line `territories the deposit has been made:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the deposit is made in any area outside the existing State, the liability shall be that of`
  line `the State of Punjab in the first instance and shall be adjusted between the successor States according to the`
  line `population ratio.`
  line
  line `(2) The liability of the existing State of Punjab in respect of any charitable or other endowment shall,`
  line `on and from the appointed day, be the liability of the successor State in whose territories the institution`
  line `entitled to the benefit of the endowment is located or of the successor State to which the objects of the`
  line `endowment, under the terms thereof, are confined.`
obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (26909)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 57
  title `Provident fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26909&sectionno=57&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `(1) The liability of the existing State of Punjab in respect of the provident fund`
  line `account of a Government servant in service on the appointed day shall, on and from that day, be the`
  line `liability of the successor State to which that Government servant is permanently allotted.`
  line
  line `(2) The liability of the existing State of Punjab in respect of the provident fund account of a`
  line `Government servant who has retired from service before the appointed day shall be the liability of the`
  line `State of Punjab in the first instance and shall be adjusted between the successor States according to the`
  line `population ratio.`
obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (26910)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 58
  title Pensions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26910&sectionno=58&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `The liability of the existing State of Punjab in respect of pensions shall pass to, or be`
  line `apportioned between, the successor States in accordance with the provisions contained in the Fourteenth`
  line Schedule.
obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  sectionId (26911)
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 59
  title Contracts.
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26911&sectionno=59&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_59_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where before the appointed day the existing State of Punjab has made any`
  line `contract in the exercise of its executive power for any purpose of the State, that contract shall be deemed`
  line `to have been made in the exercise of the executive power—`
  line
  line `(a) if the purposes of the contract are, on and from the appointed day, exclusively purposes of any`
  line `one of the successor States,—of that State; and`
  line
  line `(b) if the purposes of the contract are, on and from that day, not exclusively purposes of any one`
  line `of the successor States,—of the State of Punjab,`
  line
  line `and all rights and liabilities which have accrued, or may accrue, under any such contract shall, to the`
  line `extent to which they would have been rights or liabilities of the existing State of Punjab, be rights or`
  line `liabilities of the successor State or, as the case may be, the State of Punjab specified above:`
  line
  line `Provided that in any such case as is referred to in clause (b), the initial allocation of rights and`
  line `liabilities made by this sub-section shall be subject to such financial adjustment as may be agreed upon`
  line `between all the successor States concerned, or in default of such agreement, as the Central Government`
  line `may by order direct.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of this section, there shall be deemed to be included in the liabilities which have`
  line `accrued or may accrue under any contract—`
  line
  line `(a) any liability to satisfy an order or award made by any court or other tribunal in proceedings`
  line `relating to the contract; and`
  line
  line `(b) any liability in respect of expenses incurred in or in connection with any such proceedings.`
  line
  line `(3) This section shall have effect subject to the other provisions of this Part relating to the`
  line `apportionment of liabilities in respect of loans, guarantees and other financial obligations; and bank`
  line `balances and securities shall, notwithstanding that they partake of the nature of contractual rights, be dealt`
  line `with under those provisions.`
obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_60:
  sectionId (26912)
  sectionNo (60)
  orderNo 60
  title `Liability in respect of actionable wrong.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_60_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26912&sectionno=60&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_60_content:
  string
  line `Where, immediately before the appointed day, the`
  line `existing State of Punjab is subject to any liability in respect of an actionable wrong other than breach of`
  line `contract, that liability shall,—`
  line
  line `(a) if the cause of action arose wholly within the territories which on and from that day are the`
  line `territories of one of the successor States, be a liability of that successor State; and`
  line
  line `(b) in any other case, be initially a liability of the State of Punjab, but subject to such financial`
  line `adjustment as may be agreed upon between all the successor States concerned, or in default of such`
  line `agreement, as the Central Government may by order direct.`
obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_61:
  sectionId (26913)
  sectionNo (61)
  orderNo 61
  title `Liability as guarantor.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_61_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26913&sectionno=61&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_61_content:
  string
  line `Where, immediately before the appointed day, the existing State of`
  line `Punjab is liable as guarantor in respect of any liability of a registered co-operative society or other person,`
  line `that liability of the existing State of Punjab shall—`
  line
  line `(a) if the area of the operations of such society or person is limited to the territories which on and`
  line `from that day are the territories of one of the successor States, be a liability of that successor State;`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) in any other case, be a liability of the State of Punjab:`
  line
  line `Provided that in any such case as is referred to in clause (b) the initial allocation of liabilities under`
  line `this section shall be subject to such financial adjustment as may be agreed upon between all the successor`
  line `States, or in default of such agreement, as the Central Government may by order direct.`
obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_62:
  sectionId (26914)
  sectionNo (62)
  orderNo 62
  title `Items in suspense.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_62_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26914&sectionno=62&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_62_content:
  string
  line `If any item in suspense is ultimately found to affect an asset or liability of`
  line `the nature referred to in any of the foregoing provisions of this Part, it shall be dealt with in accordance`
  line `with that provision.`
obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_63:
  sectionId (26915)
  sectionNo (63)
  orderNo 63
  title `Residuary provision.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_63_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26915&sectionno=63&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_63_content:
  string
  line `The benefit or burden of any assets or liabilities of the existing State of`
  line `Punjab not dealt with in the foregoing provisions of this Part shall pass to the State of Punjab in the first`
  line `instance, subject to such financial adjustment as may be agreed upon between all the successor States`
  line `before the 1st day of November, 1967, or in default of such agreement, as the Central Government may`
  line `by order direct.`
obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_64:
  sectionId (26916)
  sectionNo (64)
  orderNo 64
  title `Apportionment of assets or liabilities by agreement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26916&sectionno=64&orderno=64&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_64_content:
  string
  line `Where the successor States agree that`
  line `the benefit or burden of any particular asset or liability should be apportioned between them in a manner`
  line `other than that provided for in the foregoing provisions of this Part, then, notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained therein, the benefit or burden of that asset or liability shall be apportioned in the manner agreed`
  line upon.
obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_65:
  sectionId (26917)
  sectionNo (65)
  orderNo 65
  title `Power of Central Government to order allocation or adjustment in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_65_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26917&sectionno=65&orderno=65&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_65_content:
  string
  line Where,
  line `by virtue of any of the provisions of this Part, any of the successor States becomes entitled to any`
  line `property or obtains any benefits or becomes subject to any liability, and the Central Government is of`
  line `opinion, on a reference made within a period of three years from the appointed day by any State that it is`
  line `just and equitable that that property or those benefits should be transferred to, or shared with, one or more`
  line `of the other successor States, or that a contribution towards that liability should be made by one or more`
  line `of the other successor States, the said property or benefits shall be allocated in such manner, or the other`
  line `successor State or States shall make to the State primarily subject to the liability such contribution in`
  line `respect thereof, as the Central Government may, after consultation with State Governments concerned by`
  line `order determine.`
obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_66:
  sectionId (26918)
  sectionNo (66)
  orderNo 66
  title `Certain expenditure to be charged on the Consolidated Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_66_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26918&sectionno=66&orderno=66&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_66_content:
  string
  line `All sums payable by the`
  line `Union to any State or by any State to any other State or to the Union by virtue of the provisions of this`
  line `Part, or sub-section (4) of section 72, or section 77, or Part VIII shall be charged on the Consolidated`
  line `Fund of India, or as the case may be, the Consolidated Fund of the State by which such sums are payable:`
  line
  line `Provided that where any sums are payable as aforesaid by the Union in relation to the transferred`
  line `territory, the Central Government may by order direct that sums payable in respect of such liabilities as`
  line `may be specified therein shall be charged on the Consolidated Fund of the Union territory of Himachal`
  line Pradesh.
obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_67:
  sectionId (26919)
  sectionNo (67)
  orderNo 67
  title `Provisions as to certain Corporations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_67_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26919&sectionno=67&orderno=67&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_67_content:
  string
  line `(1) The following bodies corporate constituted for the`
  line `existing State of Punjab, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the State Electricity Board constituted under the Electricity Supply Act, 1948 (54 of 1948);`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) the State Warehousing Corporation established under the Warehousing Corporations Act,`
  line `1962 (58 of 1962),`
  line
  line `shall, on and from the appointed day, continue to function in those areas in respect of which they were`
  line `functioning immediately before that day subject to the provisions of this section and to such directions as`
  line `may, from time to time, be issued by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) Any directions issued by the Central Government under sub-section (1) in respect of the Board or`
  line `the Corporation may include a direction that the Act under which the Board or the Corporation was`
  line `constituted shall, in its application to that Board or Corporation, have effect subject to such exceptions`
  line `and modifications as the Central Government thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(3) The Board or the Corporation referred to in sub-section (1) shall cease to function as from, and`
  line `shall be deemed to be dissolved on, the 1st day of November, 1967, or such earlier date as the Central`
  line `Government may, by order, appoint; and upon such dissolution, its assets, rights and liabilities shall be`
  line `apportioned between the successor States in such manner as may be agreed upon among them within one`
  line `year of the dissolution of the Board or the Corporation, as the case may be, or if no agreement is reached,`
  line `in such manner as the Central Government may, by order, determine.`
  line
  line `(4) Nothing in the preceding provisions of this section shall be construed as preventing the`
  line `Government of any of the successor States from constituting at any time on or after the appointed day, a`
  line `State Electricity Board or a State Warehousing Corporation for that State under the provisions of the Act`
  line `relating to such Board or Corporation; and if such a Board or a Corporation is so constituted in any of the`
  line `successor States before the dissolution of the Board or the Corporation referred to in sub-section (1),—`
  line
  line `(a) provision may be made by order of the Central Government enabling the new Board or the`
  line `new Corporation to take over from the existing Board or Corporation all or any of its undertakings,`
  line `assets, rights and liabilities in that State, and`
  line
  line `(b) upon the dissolution of the existing Board or Corporation, any assets, rights and liabilities`
  line `which would otherwise have passed to that State by or under the provisions of sub-section (3) shall`
  line `pass to the new Board or the new Corporation instead of to that State.`
obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_68:
  sectionId (26920)
  sectionNo (68)
  orderNo 68
  title `Continuance of arrangements in regard to generation and supply of electric power and supply of water.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26920&sectionno=68&orderno=68&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_68_content:
  string
  line `If it appears to the Central Government that the arrangement in regard to the`
  line `generation or supply of electric power or the supply of water for any area or in regard to the execution of`
  line `any project for such generation or supply has been or is likely to be modified to the disadvantage of that`
  line `area by reason of the fact that it has been transferred by the provisions of Part II from the State in which`
  line `the power stations and other installations for the generation and supply of such power, or the catchment`
  line `area, reservoirs and other works for the supply of water, as the case may be, are located, the Central`
  line `Government may give such directions as it deems fit, to the State Government or other authority`
  line `concerned for the maintenance, so far as practicable, of the previous arrangement.`
obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_69:
  sectionId (26921)
  sectionNo (69)
  orderNo 69
  title `Provisions as to Punjab State Financial Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_69_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26921&sectionno=69&orderno=69&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_69_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Punjab State Financial`
  line `Corporation Established under the State Financial Corporations Act, 1951 (53 of 1951), shall on and from`
  line `the appointed day continue to function in those areas in respect of which it was functioning immediately`
  line `before that day subject to the provisions of this section and to such directions, as may from time to time,`
  line `be issued by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) Any directions issued by the Central Government under sub-section (1) in respect of the`
  line `Corporation may include a direction that the said Act, in its application to the Corporation, shall have`
  line `effect subject to such exceptions and modifications as may be specified in the direction.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1) or sub-section (2), the Board of Directors`
  line `of the Corporation may, with the previous approval of the Central Government and shall, if so required by`
  line `the Central Government, convene at any time after the appointed day a meeting for the consideration of a`
  line `scheme for the reconstitution or reorganisation or dissolution, as the case may be, of the Corporation,`
  line `including proposals regarding the formation of new corporations and the transfer thereto of the assets,`
  line `rights and liabilities of the existing Corporation, and if such a scheme is approved at a general meeting by`
  line `a resolution passed by a majority of the shareholders present and voting, the scheme shall be submitted to`
  line `the Central Government for its sanction.`
  line
  line `(4) If the scheme is sanctioned by the Central Government either without modifications or with`
  line `modifications which are approved at a general meeting, the Central Government shall certify the scheme,`
  line `and upon such certification the scheme shall, notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in any`
  line `law for the time being in force, be binding on the Corporations affected by the scheme as well as the`
  line `shareholders and creditors thereof.`
  line
  line `(5) If the scheme is not so approved or sanctioned, the Central Government may refer the scheme to`
  line `such Judge of the High Court of Punjab and Haryana as may be nominated in this behalf by the Chief`
  line `Justice thereof and the decision of the Judge in regard to the scheme shall be final and shall be binding on`
  line `the Corporations affected by the scheme as well as the shareholders and creditors thereof.`
  line
  line `(6) Nothing in the preceding provisions of this section shall be construed as preventing the`
  line `Government of the State of Haryana or Punjab from constituting, at any time after the appointed day and`
  line `with the approval of the Central Government, a State Financial Corporation for that State under the State`
  line `Financial Corporations Act, 1951 (63 of 1951).`
obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_70:
  sectionId (26922)
  sectionNo (70)
  orderNo 70
  title `Amendment of Act 6 of 1942.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_70_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26922&sectionno=70&orderno=70&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_70_content:
  string
  line `In the Multi-Unit Co-operative Societies Act, 1942, after`
  line `section 5C, the following section shall be inserted, namely:—`
  line
  line `"5D. Transitional provision relating to certain multiunit co-operative societies.—(1) Where,`
  line `in respect of any co-operative society specified in the Fifteenth Schedule to the Punjab`
  line `Reorganisation Act, 1966, which under the provisions of sub-section (1) of section 5A would become`
  line `a multi-unit co-operative society, the Board of Directors adopts, by a majority of not less than threefourths`
  line `of the directors, any scheme for the reconstitution, reorganisation or dissolution of the society,`
  line `including proposals regarding—`
  line
  line `(a) the formation of new co-operative societies and the transfer thereto, in whole or in part, of`
  line `the assets and liabilities and employees of that society; or`
  line
  line `(b) the transfer, in whole or in part, of the assets and liabilities and employees of that society`
  line `to any other co-operative society in the existing State of Punjab or in the Union territory of`
  line `Himachal Pradesh;`
  line
  line `and the State Government of Punjab certifies the scheme at any time before the 1st day of November,`
  line `1966, then, notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (2) or sub-section (3) or sub-section (4)`
  line `of the said section or any other law, regulation or bye-law for the time being in force in relation to`
  line `that society, the scheme so certified shall be binding on all societies affected by the scheme, as well`
  line `as the shareholders, creditors and employees of all such societies, subject to such financial`
  line `adjustments as may be directed in this behalf under sub-section (3), but no such scheme shall be given`
  line `effect to before the said day:`
  line
  line `Provided that where a scheme includes any proposal regarding the transfer of assets and liabilities`
  line `and employees to any co-operative society referred to in clause (b), the scheme shall not be binding`
  line `on that existing society or the shareholders and creditors thereof, unless the proposal relating to such`
  line `transfer is accepted by the existing society by a resolution passed by a majority of the members`
  line `present at a meeting of its general body.`
  line
  line `(2) When a scheme in respect of a co-operative society is so certified, the Central Registrar shall`
  line `place the scheme at a meeting, held in such manner as may be prescribed by rules made under this Act, of`
  line `all the persons who, immediately before the date of certification of the scheme, were members of the`
  line `society, and the scheme may be approved by a resolution passed by a majority of the members present`
  line `and voting at the said meeting.`
  line
  line `(3) If the scheme is not so approved or is approved with modifications, the Central Registrar may`
  line `refer the scheme to such Judge of the High Court of Punjab and Haryana as may be nominated in this`
  line `behalf by the Chief Justice thereof and the Judge may direct such financial adjustments to be made among`
  line `the societies affected as he deems necessary, and the scheme shall be deemed to be approved subject to`
  line `those financial adjustments.`
  line
  line `(4) If, in consequence of the directions given under sub-section (3), a society becomes liable to pay`
  line `any sum of money, the successor State within whose area the society is located shall be deemed to be`
  line `guarantor in respect of the payment of such money and shall be liable as such.".`
obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_71:
  sectionId (26923)
  sectionNo (71)
  orderNo 71
  title `Provision as to co-operative banks.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_71_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26923&sectionno=71&orderno=71&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_71_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in section 22 of the`
  line `Banking Regulation Act, 1949 (10 of 1949), where on account of the reorganisation of the existing State`
  line `of Punjab, a co-operative bank is newly formed on the appointed day or within three months thereof in`
  line `any of the successor States, it may commence and conduct banking business without obtaining a licence`
  line `under that section from the Reserve Bank of India, until it is granted such a licence or until it is informed`
  line `by the Reserve Bank of India that such a licence cannot be granted to it;`
  line
  line `Provided that such bank applies to the Reserve Bank of India for such a licence within a period of`
  line `three months from the date of formation of the bank.`
obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_72:
  sectionId (26924)
  sectionNo (72)
  orderNo 72
  title `General provisions as to statutory corporations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_72_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26924&sectionno=72&orderno=72&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_72_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as otherwise expressly provided by`
  line `the foregoing provisions of this Part, where any body corporate constituted under a Central Act, State Act`
  line `or Provincial Act for the existing State of Punjab or any part thereof serves the needs of the successor`
  line `States or has, by virtue of the provisions of Part II, become an inter-State body corporate, then, the body`
  line `corporate shall, on and from the appointed day, continue to function and operate in those areas in respect`
  line `of which it was functioning and operating immediately before that day, subject to such directions as may`
  line `from time to time be issued by the Central Government, until other provisions is made by law in respect`
  line `of the said body corporate.`
  line
  line `(2) Any direction issued by the Central Government under sub-section (1) in respect of any such body`
  line `corporate may include a direction that any law by which the said body corporate is governed shall, in its`
  line `application to that body corporate, have effect, subject to such exceptions and modifications as may be`
  line `specified in the direction.`
  line
  line `(3) For the removal of doubt it is hereby declared that the provisions of this section shall apply also to`
  line `the Punjab University constituted under the Punjab University Act, 1947 (East Punjab Act 7 of 1947), the`
  line `Punjab Agricultural University constituted under the Punjab Agricultural University Act, 1961 (Punjab`
  line `Act 32 of 1961), and the Board constituted under the provisions of Part III of the Sikh Gurdwaras Act,`
  line `1925 (Punjab Act 8 of 1925).`
  line
  line `(4) For the purpose of giving effect to the provisions of this section in so far as it relates to the Punjab`
  line `University and the Punjab Agricultural University referred to in sub-section (3) the successor States shall`
  line `make such grants as the Central Government may, from time to time, by order, determine.`
obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_73:
  sectionId (26925)
  sectionNo (73)
  orderNo 73
  title `Provision as to certain companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_73_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26925&sectionno=73&orderno=73&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_73_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in the foregoing`
  line `provisions of this Part, each of the following companies, namely:—`
  line
  line `(i) the Punjab Export Corporation;`
  line
  line `(ii) the Punjab State Small Industries Corporation;`
  line
  line `(iii) the Punjab Dairy Development Corporation;`
  line
  line `(iv) the Punjab Poultry Corporation;`
  line
  line `(v) the Land Development and Seed Corporation;`
  line
  line `(vi) the Industrial Development Corporation; and`
  line
  line `(vii) the Agro-Industrial Corporation,`
  line
  line `shall, on and from the appointed day and until otherwise provided for in any law, or in any agreement`
  line `among the successor States, or in any direction issued by the Central Government, continue to function in`
  line `the areas in which it was functioning immediately before that day; and the Central Government may from`
  line `time to time issue such directions in relation to such functioning as it may deem fit, notwithstanding`
  line `anything to the contrary contained in the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956), or in any other law.`
  line
  line `(2) Any directions issued under sub-section (1) in respect of a company referred to in that sub-section,`
  line `may include directions—`
  line
  line `(a) regarding the division of the interests and shares of the existing State of Punjab in the`
  line `company among the successor States;`
  line
  line `(b) requiring the reconstitution of the Board of Directors of the company so as to give adequate`
  line `representation to all the successor States.`
obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_74:
  sectionId (26926)
  sectionNo (74)
  orderNo 74
  title `Temporary provisions as to continuance of certain existing road transport permits.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_74_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26926&sectionno=74&orderno=74&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_74_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in section 63 of the Motor Vehicles Act, 1939 (4 of 1939), a permit`
  line `granted by the State or a Regional Transport Authority in the existing State of Punjab shall, if such permit`
  line `was, immediately before the appointed day, valid and effective in any area therein, be deemed to continue`
  line `to be valid and effective in that area after that day subject to the provisions of that Act as for the time`
  line `being in force in that area and it shall not be necessary for any such permit to be countersigned by any`
  line `State or Regional Transport Authority for the purpose of validating it for use in such area:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may, after consultation with the State Government or`
  line `Governments concerned, add to, amend or vary the conditions attached to the permit by the authority by`
  line `which the permit was granted.`
  line
  line `(2) No tolls, entrance fees or other charges of a like nature shall be levied after the appointed day in`
  line `respect of any transport vehicle for its operations in any of the successor States under any such permit, if`
  line `such vehicle was immediately before that day exempt from the payment of any such toll, entrance fees or`
  line `other charges for its operations within the existing State of Punjab:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may, after consultation with the State Government or`
  line `Governments concerned, authorise the levy of any such toll, entrance fees or other charges, as the case`
  line `may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_75:
  sectionId (26927)
  sectionNo (75)
  orderNo 75
  title `Special provision relating to retrenchment compensation in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_75_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26927&sectionno=75&orderno=75&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_75_content:
  string
  line `Where, on`
  line `account of the reorganisation of the existing State of Punjab under this Act, any body corporate`
  line `constituted under a Central Act, State Act or Provincial Act, any co-operative society registered under any`
  line `law relating to co-operative societies or any commercial or industrial undertaking of that State is`
  line `reconstituted or reorganised in any manner whatsoever or is amalgamated with any other body corporate,`
  line `co-operative society or undertaking, or is dissolved and in consequence of such reconstitution,`
  line `reorganisation, amalgamation or dissolution, any workman employed by such body corporate or any such`
  line `co-operative society or undertaking, is transferred to, or re-employed by any other body corporate, or in`
  line `any other co-operative society or undertaking then notwithstanding anything contained in section 25F,`
  line `25FF or 25FFF, of the Industrial Disputes Act, 1947 (14 of 1947), such transfer or re-employment shall`
  line `not entitle him to any compensation under that section:`
  line
  line `Provided that—`
  line
  line `(a) the terms and conditions of service applicable to the workman after such transfer or`
  line `re-employment are not less favourable to the workman than those applicable to him immediately`
  line `before the transfer or re-employment; and`
  line
  line `(b) the employer in relation to the body corporate, the cooperative society or the undertaking`
  line `where the workman transferred or re-employed is, by agreement or otherwise, legally liable to pay to`
  line `the workman, in the event of his retrenchment, compensation under section 25F, 25FF or 25FFF of`
  line `the Industrial Disputes Act, 1947 (14 of 1947), on the basis that his service has been continuous and`
  line `has not been interrupted by the transfer or re-employment.`
obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_76:
  sectionId (26928)
  sectionNo (76)
  orderNo 76
  title `Special provision as to income-tax.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_76_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26928&sectionno=76&orderno=76&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_76_content:
  string
  line `Where the assets, rights and liabilities of any body`
  line `corporate carrying on business are, under the provisions of this Part, transferred to any other bodies`
  line `corporate which after the transfer carry on the same business, the losses of profits or gains sustained by`
  line `the body corporate first mentioned which, but for such transfer, would have been allowed to be carried`
  line `forward and set off in accordance with the provisions of Chapter VI of the Income-tax Act, 1961 (43 of`
  line `1961), shall be apportioned amongst the transferee bodies corporate in accordance with the rules to be made by the Central Government in this behalf and, upon such apportionment, the share of loss allotted to`
  line `each transferee body corporate shall be dealt with in accordance with the provisions of Chapter VI of the`
  line `said Act as if the transferee body corporate had itself sustained such loss in a business carried on by it in`
  line `the years in which these losses were sustained.`
obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_77:
  sectionId (26929)
  sectionNo (77)
  orderNo 77
  title `Continuance of facilities in certain State institutions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_77_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26929&sectionno=77&orderno=77&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_77_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Government of the State of`
  line `Haryana or Punjab, or, as the case may be, the Central Government in relation to the transferred territory`
  line `or the Union territory of Chandigarh, shall in respect of the institutions specified in the Sixteenth`
  line `Schedule located in the State or territory aforesaid continue to provide facilities to any other Government`
  line `aforesaid and the people of the States and territories aforesaid which shall not, in any respect, be less`
  line `favourable to such Government and people than what were being provided to them before the appointed`
  line `day for such period and upon such terms and conditions (including those relating to any contributions to`
  line `be made for the provision of such facilities) as may be agreed upon between the said Governments before`
  line `the 1st day of April, 1967, or if no agreement is reached by the said date, as may be fixed by order of the`
  line `Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may, at any time before the 1st day of April, 1967, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, specify in the Sixteenth Schedule any other institution existing on the appointed day in`
  line `the said States and territories and on the issue of such notification, the Schedule shall be deemed to be`
  line `amended by the inclusion of the said institution therein.`
obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_78:
  sectionId (26930)
  sectionNo (78)
  orderNo 78
  title `Rights and liabilities in regard to Bhakra-Nangal and Beas Projects.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_78_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26930&sectionno=78&orderno=78&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_78_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding`
  line `anything contained in this Act but subject to the provisions of sections 79 and 80, all rights and liabilities`
  line `of the existing State of Punjab in relation to Bhakra-Nangal Project and Beas Project shall, on the`
  line `appointed day, be the rights and liabilities of the successor States in such proportion as may be fixed, and`
  line `subject to such adjustments as may be made, by agreement entered into by the said States after`
  line `consultation with the Central Government or, if no such agreement is entered into within two years of the`
  line `appointed day, as the Central Government may by order determine having regard to the purposes of the`
  line `Projects:`
  line
  line `Provided that the order so made by the Central Government may be varied by any subsequent`
  line `agreement entered into by the successor States after consultation with the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) An agreement or order referred to in sub-section (1) shall, if there has been an extension or further`
  line `development of either of the projects referred to in that sub-section after the appointed day, provide also`
  line `for the rights and liabilities of the successor States in relation to such extension or further development.`
  line
  line `(3) The rights and liabilities referred to in sub-sections (1) and (2) shall include`
  line
  line `(a) the rights to receive and to utilise the water available for distribution as a result of the`
  line `projects, and`
  line
  line `(b) the rights to receive and to utilise the power generated as a result of the projects,`
  line
  line `but shall not include the rights and liabilities under any contract entered into before the appointed day by`
  line `the Government of the existing State of Punjab with any person or authority other than Government.`
  line
  line `(4) In this section and in sections 79 and 80,—`
  line
  line `(A) "Beas Project" means the works which are either under construction or are to be constructed`
  line `as components of the Beas-Sutlej Link Project (Unit I) and Pong Dam Project on the Beas river`
  line `(Unit II) including—`
  line
  line `(i) Beas-Sutlej Link Project (Unit I) comprising—`
  line
  line `(a) Pandoh Dam and works appurtenant thereto,`
  line
  line `(b) Pandoh-Baggi Tunnel,`
  line
  line `(c) Sundernagar Hydel Channel,`
  line
  line `(d) Sundernagar-Sutlej Tunnel,`
  line
  line `(e) By-pass Tunnel,`
  line
  line `(f) four generating units each of 165 M.W. capacity at Dehar Power House on the right`
  line `side of Sutlej river,`
  line
  line `(g) fifth generating unit of 120 M.W. capacity at Bhakra Right Bank Power House,`
  line
  line `(h) transmission lines,`
  line
  line `(i) Balancing Reservoir;`
  line
  line `(ii) Pong Dam Project (Unit II) comprising—`
  line
  line `(a) Pong Dam and works appurtenant thereto,`
  line
  line `(b) Outlet Works,`
  line
  line `(c) Penstock Tunnels,`
  line
  line `(d) Power plant with four generating units of 60 M.W. each;`
  line
  line `(iii) such other works as are ancillary to the works aforesaid and are of common interest to`
  line `more than one State;`
  line
  line `(B) "Bhakra-Nangal Project" means—`
  line
  line `(i) Bhakra Dam, Reservoir and works appurtenant thereto;`
  line
  line `(ii) Nangal Dam and Nangal-Hydel Channel;`
  line
  line `(iii) Bhakra Main Line and canal system;`
  line
  line `(iv) Bhakra Left Bank Power House, Ganguwal Power House and Kotla Power House,`
  line `switchyards, sub-stations and transmission lines;`
  line
  line `(v) Bhakra Right Bank Power House with four units of 120 M.W. each.`
obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_79:
  sectionId (26931)
  sectionNo (79)
  orderNo 79
  title `Bhakra Management Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_79_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26931&sectionno=79&orderno=79&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_79_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall constitute a Board to be called`
  line `the Bhakra Management Board for the administration, maintenance and operation of the following works,`
  line `namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) Bhakra Dam and Reservior and works appurtenant thereto;`
  line
  line `(b) Nangal Dam and Nangal-Hydel Channel up to Kotla Power House;`
  line
  line `(c) the irrigation headworks at Rupar, Harike and Ferozepur;`
  line
  line `(d) Bhakra Power Houses:`
  line
  line `Provided that the administration, maintenance and operation by the said Board of the generating`
  line `units of the Right Bank Power House as have not been commissioned shall commence as and when`
  line `any such unit has been commissioned;`
  line
  line `(e) Ganguwal and Kotla Power Houses;`
  line
  line `(f) Sub-stations at Ganguwal, Ambala, Panipat, Delhi, Ludhiana, Sangrur and Hissar and the main`
  line `220 KV transmission lines connecting the said sub-stations with the power stations specified in`
  line `clauses (d) and (e); and`
  line
  line `(g) such other works as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line specify.
  line
  line `(2) The Bhakra Management Board shall consist of—`
  line
  line `(a) a whole-time Chairman and two whole-time members to be appointed by the Central`
  line Government;
  line
  line `(b) a representative each of the Governments of the States of Punjab, Haryana and Rajasthan and`
  line `the Union territory of Himachal Pradesh to be nominated by the respective Governments or`
  line `Administrator, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(c) two representatives of the Central Government to be nominated by that Government.`
  line
  line `(3) The functions of the Bhakra Management Board shall include—`
  line
  line `(a) the regulation of the supply of water from the Bhakra-Nangal Project to the States of Haryana,`
  line `Punjab and Rajasthan having regard to—`
  line
  line `(i) any agreement entered into or arrangement made between the Governments of the existing`
  line `State of Punjab and the State of Rajasthan, and`
  line
  line `(ii) the agreement or the order referred to in sub-section (1) of section 78;`
  line
  line `(b) the regulation of the supply of power generated at the power houses referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1) to any Electricity Board or other authority in charge of the distribution of power`
  line `having regard to—`
  line
  line `(i) any agreement entered into or arrangement made between the Governments of the existing`
  line `State of Punjab and the State of Rajasthan,`
  line
  line `(ii) the agreement or the order referred to in sub-section (1) of section 78; and`
  line
  line `(iii) any agreement entered into or arrangement made by the existing State of Punjab or the`
  line `Punjab Electricity Board or the State of Rajasthan or the Rajasthan Electricity Board with any`
  line `other Electricity Board or authority in charge of distribution of power before the appointed day in`
  line `relation to the supply of power generated at the power houses specified in sub-section (1);`
  line
  line `(c) the construction of such of the remaining works connected with the Right Bank Power House`
  line `as the Central Government may specify;`
  line
  line `(d) such other functions as the Central Government may, after consultation with the Governments`
  line `of the States of Haryana, Punjab and Rajasthan, entrust to it.`
  line
  line `(4) The Bhakra Management Board may employ such staff as it may consider necessary for the`
  line `efficient discharge of its functions under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that every person who immediately before the constitution of the said Board was engaged in`
  line `the construction, maintenance or operator of the works in sub-section (1) shall continue to be so employed`
  line `under the Board in connection with the said works on the same terms and conditions of service as were`
  line `applicable to him before such constitution until the Central Government by order directs otherwise:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the said Board may at any time in consultation with State Government or the`
  line `Electricity Board concerned and with the previous approval of the Central Government return any such`
  line `person for service under that Government or Board.`
  line
  line `(5) The Governments of the successor States and of Rajasthan shall at all times provide the necessary`
  line `funds to the Bhakra Management Board to meet all expenses (including the salaries and allowances of the`
  line `staff) required for the discharge of its functions and such amounts shall be apportioned among the`
  line `successor States, the State of Rajasthan and Electricity Boards of the said States in such proportion as the`
  line `Central Government may, having regard to the benefits to each of the said States or Boards, specify.`
  line
  line `(6) The Bhakra Management Board shall be under the control of the Central Government and shall`
  line `comply with such directions, as may from time to time, be given to it by that Government.`
  line
  line `(7) The Bhakra Management Board may with the approval of the Central Government delegate such`
  line `of its powers, functions and duties as it may deem fit to the Chairman of the said Board or to any officer`
  line `subordinate to the Board.`
  line
  line `(8) The Central Government may, for the purpose of enabling the Bhakra Management Board to`
  line `function effectively, issue such directions to the State Governments of Haryana, Punjab and Rajasthan and the Administrator of the Union territory of Himachal Pradesh or any other authority, and the State`
  line `Governments, Administrator or authority shall comply with such directions.`
  line
  line `(9) The Bhakra Management Board may, with the previous approval of the Central Government and`
  line `by notification in the Official Gazette, make regulations consistent with this Act and the rules made`
  line `thereunder, to provide for—`
  line
  line `(a) regulating the time and place of meetings of the Board and the procedure to be followed for`
  line `the transaction of business at such meetings;`
  line
  line `(b) delegation of powers and duties to the Chairman or any officer of the Board;`
  line
  line `(c) the appointment, and the regulation of the conditions of service, of the officers and other staff`
  line `of the Board;`
  line
  line `(d) any other matter for which regulations are considered necessary by the Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_80:
  sectionId (26932)
  sectionNo (80)
  orderNo 80
  title `Construction of Beas Project.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_80_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26932&sectionno=80&orderno=80&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_80_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act or in any`
  line `other law, the construction (including the completion of any work already commenced) of the Beas`
  line `Project shall, on and from the appointed day, be undertaken by the Central Government on behalf of the`
  line `successor States and the State of Rajasthan:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Governments of the successor States and the State of Rajasthan shall at all times`
  line `provide the necessary funds to the Central Government for the expenditure on the project [including the`
  line `expenses of the Board referred to in sub-section (2)] and such amounts shall be apportioned among the`
  line `successor States and the State of Rajasthan in such proportion as may be fixed by the Central Government`
  line
  line `after consultation with the Governments of the said States.`
  line
  line `(2) For the discharge of its functions under sub-section (1), the Central Government may—`
  line
  line `(a) by notification in the Official Gazette and in consultation with the Governments of the`
  line `successor States and the State of Rajasthan, constitute a Board to be called the Beas Construction`
  line `Board with such members as it may deem fit and assign to the Board such functions as it may`
  line `consider necessary; and`
  line
  line `(b) issue such directions to the State Governments of Haryana, Punjab and Rajasthan and the`
  line `Administrator of the Union territory of Himachal Pradesh or any other authority, and the State`
  line `Governments, Administrator or other authority shall comply with such directions.`
  line
  line `(3) The notification constituting a Board under clause (a) of sub-section (2) may empower the Board`
  line `to appoint such staff as may be necessary for the efficient discharge of its functions:`
  line
  line `Provided that every person who immediately before the constitution of the Board was engaged in the`
  line `construction or any work relating to the Beas Project shall continue to be so employed by the Board in`
  line `connection with the said works on the same terms and conditions of service as were applicable to him`
  line `before such constitution until the Central Government by order directs otherwise:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Board may at any time in consultation with the State Government or the`
  line `Electricity Board concerned and with the previous approval of the Central Government return any such`
  line `person for service under that Government or Board.`
  line
  line `(4) Nothing contained in this section shall be construed as enabling the Central Government to reduce`
  line `or enlarge the scope of the Beas Project as agreed to between the Governments of the State of Rajasthan`
  line `and the existing State of Punjab except after consultation with the Governments of the States of Haryana,`
  line `Punjab and Rajasthan.`
  line
  line `(5) Any component of the Beas Project in relation to which the construction has been completed after`
  line `the appointed day may be transferred by the Central Government to the Board constituted under section`
  line `79 whereupon the provisions of that section shall apply as if it were a work included in sub-section (1) of`
  line `that section.`
  line
  line `(6) The Bhakra Management Board constituted under section 79 shall be re-named as the Bhakra`
  line `Beas Management Board when any of the components of the Beas Project has been transferred under sub-section (5), and the Beas Construction Board shall cease to exist when all the components of the Beas`
  line `Project have been so transferred.`
obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_81:
  sectionId (26933)
  sectionNo (81)
  orderNo 81
  title `Provisions relating to All-India Services.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_81_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26933&sectionno=81&orderno=81&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_81_content:
  string
  line `(1) In this section, the expression “State cadre”—`
  line
  line `(a) in relation to the Indian Administrative Service, has the meaning assigned to it in the Indian`
  line `Administrative Service (Cadre) Rules, 1954, and`
  line
  line `(b) in relation to the Indian Police Service, has the meaning assigned to it in the Indian Police`
  line `Service (Cadre) Rules, 1954.`
  line
  line `(2) In place of the cadres of the Indian Administrative Service and the Indian Police Service for the`
  line `existing State of Punjab, there shall, on and from the appointed day, be two separate cadres, one for the`
  line `State of Punjab and the other for the State of Haryana, in respect of each of these Services.`
  line
  line `(3) The initial strength and composition of each of the State cadres for the States of Punjab and`
  line `Haryana and the strength and composition of the Delhi-Himachal Pradesh State cadres shall be such as`
  line `the Central Government may, by order, determine before the appointed day.`
  line
  line `(4) The members of each of the said Services borne on the State cadres for the existing State of`
  line `Punjab immediately before the appointed day shall be allocated to the State cadres of the same Service for`
  line `each of the States of Punjab and Haryana and to the Delhi-Himachal Pradesh State cadres in such manner`
  line `and with effect from such date or dates as the Central Government may, by order, specify.`
  line
  line `(5) Nothing in this section shall be deemed to affect the operation, on or after the appointed day, of`
  line `the All-India Services Act, 1951 (61 of 1951), or the rules made thereunder in relation to the State cadres`
  line `of the said Services referred to in sub-section (3) and in relation to the members of those Services borne`
  line `on the said cadres.`
obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_82:
  sectionId (26934)
  sectionNo (82)
  orderNo 82
  title `Provisions relating to other Services.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_82_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26934&sectionno=82&orderno=82&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_82_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every person who immediately before the appointed`
  line `day is serving in connection with the affairs of the existing State of Punjab shall, on and from that day,`
  line `provisionally continue to serve in connection with the affairs of the State of Punjab unless he is required,`
  line `by general or special order of the Central Government, to serve provisionally in connection with the`
  line `affairs of any other successor State.`
  line
  line `(2) As soon as may be after the appointed day, the Central Government shall, by general or special`
  line `order, determine the successor State to which every person referred to in sub-section (1) shall be finally`
  line `allotted for service and the date with effect from which such allotment shall take effect or be deemed to`
  line `have taken effect.`
  line
  line `(3) Every person who is finally allotted under the provisions of sub-section (2) to a successor State`
  line `shall, if he is not already serving therein, be made available for serving in the successor State from such`
  line `date as may be agreed upon between the Governments concerned or in default of such agreement, as may`
  line `be determined by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government may, by order, establish one or more advisory committees for the`
  line `purpose of assisting it in regard to—`
  line
  line `(a) the division and integration of the services among the successor States; and`
  line
  line `(b) the ensuring of fair and equitable treatment to all persons affected by the provisions of this`
  line `section and the proper consideration of any representations made by such persons.`
  line
  line `(5) The foregoing provisions of this section shall not apply in relation to any person to whom the`
  line `provisions of section 81 apply.`
  line
  line `(6) Nothing in this section shall be deemed to affect on or after the appointed day the operation of the`
  line `provisions of Chapter I of Part XIV of the Constitution in relation to the determination of the conditions`
  line `of service of persons serving in connection with the affairs of the Union or any State:`
  line
  line `Provided that the conditions of service applicable immediately before the appointed day to the case of`
  line `any person referred to in sub- section (1) or sub-section (2) shall not be varied to his disadvantage except`
  line `with the previous approval of the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_83:
  sectionId (26935)
  sectionNo (83)
  orderNo 83
  title `Provisions as to continuance of officers in the same post.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_83_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26935&sectionno=83&orderno=83&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_83_content:
  string
  line `Every person who immediately`
  line `before the appointed day is holding or discharging the duties of any post or office in connection with the`
  line `affairs of the existing State of Punjab in any area which on that day falls within any of the successor`
  line `States shall continue to hold the same post or office in that successor State and shall be deemed, on and`
  line `from that day, to have been duly appointed to the post or office by the Government of, or other`
  line `appropriate authority in, that successor State:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this section shall be deemed to prevent a competent authority on or after the`
  line `appointed day from passing in relation to such person any order affecting his continuance in such post or`
  line office.
obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_84:
  sectionId (26936)
  sectionNo (84)
  orderNo 84
  title `Power of Central Government to give directions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_84_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26936&sectionno=84&orderno=84&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_84_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may give such`
  line `directions to the State Governments of Punjab and Haryana and to the Administrators of the Union`
  line `terriories of Himachal Pradesh and Chandigarh as may appear to it to be necessary for the purpose of`
  line `giving effect to the foregoing provisions of this Part and the State Governments and the Administrators`
  line `shall comply with such directions.`
obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_85:
  sectionId (26937)
  sectionNo (85)
  orderNo 85
  title `Provisions as to State Public Service Commissions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_85_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26937&sectionno=85&orderno=85&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_85_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Public Service Commission for`
  line `the existing State of Punjab shall, on and from the appointed day, cease to exist.`
  line
  line `(2) The person holding office immediately before the appointed day as Chairman of the Public`
  line `Service Commission for the existing State of Punjab shall become the Chairman of the Public Service`
  line `Commission for the State of Haryana or Punjab as the President shall, by order, specify and every other`
  line `person holding office immediately before that day as member of that Commission shall become a`
  line `member, or if so specified by the President, the Chairman, of such one of the said Commissions as the`
  line `President shall, by order, specify.`
  line
  line `(3) Every person who becomes the Chairman or other member of a Public Service Commission on the`
  line `appointed day under sub-section (2) shall—`
  line
  line `(a) be entitled to receive from the Government of the State conditions of service not less`
  line `favourable than those to which he was entitled under the provisions applicable to him immediately`
  line `before the appointed day;`
  line
  line `(b) subject to the proviso to clause (2) of article 316, hold office or continue to hold office until`
  line `the expiration of his term of office as determined under the provisions applicable to him immediately`
  line `before the appointed day.`
  line
  line `(4) The report of the Punjab Public Service Commission as to the work done by the Commission in`
  line `respect of any period prior to the appointed day shall be presented under clause (2) of article 323 to the`
  line `Governors of Punjab and Haryana, and the Governor of Punjab shall, on receipt of such report, cause a`
  line `copy thereof together with a memorandum explaining as far as possible, as respects the cases, if any,`
  line `where the advice of the Commission was not accepted, the reasons for such non-acceptance to be laid`
  line `before the Legislature of the State of Punjab and it shall not be necessary to cause such report or any such`
  line `memorandum to be laid before the Legislative Assembly of Haryana.`
obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_86:
  sectionId (26938)
  sectionNo (86)
  orderNo 86
  title `Amendment of Act 37 of 1956.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_86_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26938&sectionno=86&orderno=86&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_86_content:
  string
  line `In clause (a) of section 15 of the States Reorganisation Act,`
  line 1956,—
  line
  line `(i)for the word “Punjab”, the words “Haryana, Punjab” shall be substituted;`
  line
  line `(ii) for the words “and Himachal Pradesh”, the words “Himachal Pradesh and Chandigarh” shall be substituted.`
obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_87:
  sectionId (26939)
  sectionNo (87)
  orderNo 87
  title `Power to extend enactments to Chandigarh.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_87_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26939&sectionno=87&orderno=87&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_87_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, by notification in`
  line `the Official Gazette, extend with such restrictions or modifications as it thinks fit, to the Union territory of`
  line `Chandigarh any enactment which is in force in a State at the date of the notification.`
obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_88:
  sectionId (26940)
  sectionNo (88)
  orderNo 88
  title `Territorial extent of laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_88_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26940&sectionno=88&orderno=88&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_88_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of Part II shall not be deemed to have effected any`
  line `change in the territories to which any law in force immediately before the appointed day extends or`
  line `applies, and territorial references in any such law to the State of Punjab shall, until otherwise provided by`
  line `a competent Legislature or other competent authority, be construed as meaning the territories within that`
  line `State immediately before the appointed day.`
obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_89:
  sectionId (26941)
  sectionNo (89)
  orderNo 89
  title `Power to adapt laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_89_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_89_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26941&sectionno=89&orderno=89&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_89_content:
  string
  line `For the purpose of facilitating the application in relation to the State of`
  line `Punjab or Haryana or to the Union territory of Himachal Pradesh or Chandigarh of any law made before`
  line `the appointed day, the appropriate Government may, before the expiration of two years from that day, by`
  line `order, make such adaptations and modifications of the law, whether by way of repeal or amendment, as`
  line `may be necessary or expedient, and thereupon every such law shall have effect subject to the adaptations`
  line `and modifications so made until altered, repealed or amended by a competent legislature or other`
  line `competent authority.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—In this section, the expression “appropriate Government” means—`
  line
  line `(a) as respects any law relating to a matter enumerated in the Union List, the Central`
  line `Government; and`
  line
  line `(b) as respects any other law,—`
  line
  line `(i) in its application to a State, the State Government, and`
  line
  line `(ii) in its application to a Union territory, the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_89_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_90:
  sectionId (26942)
  sectionNo (90)
  orderNo 90
  title `Power to construe laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_90_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26942&sectionno=90&orderno=90&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_90_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding that no provision or insufficient provision has`
  line `been made under section 89 for the adaptation of a law made before the appointed day, any court, tribunal`
  line `or authority, required or empowered to enforce such law may, for the purpose of facilitating its`
  line `application in relation to the State of Punjab or Haryana, or to the Union territory of Himachal Pradesh or`
  line `Chandigarh construe the law in such manner, without affecting the substance, as may be necessary or`
  line `proper in regard to the matter before the court, tribunal or authority.`
  line
  line `(2) Any reference to the High Court of Punjab in any law shall, unless the context otherwise requires,`
  line `be construed, on and from the appointed day, as a reference to the High Court of Punjab and Haryana.`
obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_91:
  sectionId (26943)
  sectionNo (91)
  orderNo 91
  title `Power to name authorities, etc., for exercising statutory functions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_91_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_91_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26943&sectionno=91&orderno=91&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_91_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government,`
  line `as respects the Union territory of Chandigarh or the transferred territory, and the Government of the State`
  line `of Haryana as respects the territories thereof may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify the`
  line `authority, officer or person who, on and from the appointed day, shall be competent to exercise such`
  line `functions exercisable under any law in force on that day as may be mentioned in that notification and such`
  line `law shall have effect accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_91_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_92:
  sectionId (26944)
  sectionNo (92)
  orderNo 92
  title `Legal proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_92_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_92_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26944&sectionno=92&orderno=92&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_92_content:
  string
  line `Where, immediately before the appointed day, the existing State of Punjab`
  line `is a party to any legal proceedings with respect to any property, rights or liabilities subject to`
  line `apportionment under this Act, the successor State which succeeds to, or acquires a share in, that property`
  line `or those rights or liabilities by virtue of any provision of this Act shall be deemed to be substituted for the`
  line `existing State of Punjab or added as a party to those proceedings, and the proceedings may continue`
  line accordingly.
obj_root_law_sections_92_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_93:
  sectionId (26945)
  sectionNo (93)
  orderNo 93
  title `Transfer of pending proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_93_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_93_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26945&sectionno=93&orderno=93&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_93_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every proceeding pending immediately before the`
  line `appointed day before a court (other than a High Court), tribunal, authority or officer in any area which on`
  line `that day falls within a State or Union territory shall, if it is a proceeding relating exclusively to the`
  line `territories which as from that day are the territories of another State or Union territory, stand transferred to`
  line `the corresponding court, tribunal, authority or officer in that other State or Union territory, as the case`
  line `may be.`
  line
  line `(2) If any question arises as to whether any proceeding should stand transferred under sub-section (1),`
  line `it shall be referred to the High Court having jurisdiction in respect of the area in which the court, tribunal, authority or officer before which or whom such proceeding is pending on the appointed day, is`
  line `functioning, and the decision of that High Court shall be final.`
  line
  line `(3) In this section—`
  line
  line `(a) “proceeding” includes any suit, case or appeal; and`
  line
  line `(b) “corresponding court, tribunal, authority or officer” in a State or a Union territory means—`
  line
  line `(i) the court, tribunal, authority or officer in that State or a Union territory in which or before`
  line `whom, the proceeding would have lain if it had been instituted after the appointed day; or`
  line
  line `(ii) in case of doubt, such court, tribunal, authority or officer in that State or Union territory,`
  line `as may be determined after the appointed day by the Government of that State or the Central`
  line `Government, as the case may be, or before the appointed day by the Government of the existing`
  line `State of Punjab, to be the corresponding court, tribunal, authority or officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_93_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_94:
  sectionId (26946)
  sectionNo (94)
  orderNo 94
  title `Right of pleaders to practise in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_94_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_94_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26946&sectionno=94&orderno=94&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_94_content:
  string
  line `Any person who, immediately before the`
  line `appointed day, is enrolled as a pleader entitled to practise in any subordinate courts in the existing State of`
  line `Punjab shall, for a period of one year from that day, continue to be entitled to practise in those courts,`
  line `notwithstanding that the whole or any part of the territories within the jurisdiction of those courts has`
  line `been transferred to the State of Haryana or to a Union territory.`
obj_root_law_sections_94_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_95:
  sectionId (26947)
  sectionNo (95)
  orderNo 95
  title `Effect of provisions of the Act inconsistent with other laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_95_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_95_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26947&sectionno=95&orderno=95&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_95_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act shall`
  line `have effect notwithstanding anything inconsistent therewith contained in any other law.`
obj_root_law_sections_95_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_96:
  sectionId (26948)
  sectionNo (96)
  orderNo 96
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_96_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_96_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26948&sectionno=96&orderno=96&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_96_content:
  string
  line `If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of this`
  line `Act, the President may, by order, do anything not inconsistent with such provisions which appears to him`
  line `to be necessary or expedient for the purpose of removing the difficulty.`
obj_root_law_sections_96_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_97:
  sectionId (26949)
  sectionNo (97)
  orderNo 97
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_97_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 1986, s. 2 and the Schedule, for certain words (w.e.f. 15-5-1986).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807&sectionId=26949&sectionno=97&orderno=97&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00014_196631_1517807319807
obj_root_law_sections_97_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules to give effect to the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the procedure to be followed by the Bhakra Management Board and the Beas Construction`
  line `Board for the conduct of business and for the proper functioning of the Boards and the manner of`
  line `filling casual vacancies among the members of the said Boards;`
  line
  line `(b) the salaries and allowances to be paid to the whole-time Chairman and whole-time members`
  line `of the Bhakra Management Board;`
  line
  line `(c) the salaries and allowances and other conditions of service of the members of the staff of the`
  line `Bhakra Management Board or the Beas Construction Board;`
  line
  line `(d) the maintenance of records of all business transacted at the meetings of the Bhakra`
  line `Management Board or the Beas Construction Board and the submission of copies of such records to`
  line `the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(e) the conditions subject to which, and the mode in which, contracts may be made on behalf of`
  line `the successor States and the State of Rajasthan in relation to the functions of the Bhakra Management`
  line `Board or the Beas Construction Board;`
  line
  line `(f) the preparation of the budget estimates of the receipts and expenditure of the said Boards and`
  line `the authority by which such estimates shall be approved;`
  line
  line `(g) the conditions subject to which the said Boards may incur expenditure or re-appropriate funds`
  line `from any budget head to another such head;`
  line
  line `(h) the preparation and submission of annual reports;`
  line
  line `(i) the maintenance of accounts of the expenditure incurred by the said Boards;`
  line
  line `(j) any other matter which is to be, or may be, prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament while it is in session for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one`
  line `session or ^1`
  line `in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only`
  line `in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be, so however that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validly of anything previously done under that rule.`
